      "$description": "Warm Gold — the Klyp BRAND ACCENT (restored 2026-06-29, Val — the iris purple swap was reverted; the `iris` scale was retired and its values moved to `purple`). Re-anchored on the pastel Klyp gold #FDD59A = gold.700 (⭐ solid accent → --color-accent). On dark the accent FILL pairs with DARK text (--color-fg-inverse, ~13:1); as fg/icon on dark, gold.700 reads ~13.8:1. 100=darkest → 1000=lightest, OKLCH hue ~77°: prior gold chroma taper, lightness re-anchored so 700 = #FDD59A exactly. Semantic accent maps gold.700/800/600/500."
